21/04/2006
KABUL, Afghanistan -- Croatian Foreign Minister Kolinda Grabar-Kitarovic reaffirmed her country's support for the democratisation and stabilisation of Afghanistan, as she kicked off a two-day visit to Kabul on Thursday (20 April). 
She held separate talks with Afghan counterpart Abudullah Abdullah, President Hamid Karzai and Women's Rights Minister Massouda Jalal. 
The focus was on ways to enhance bilateral ties in the political and economic sectors, and on Zagreb's plans to open a diplomatic mission in Kabul. 
Grabar-Kitarovic also announced that Croatia plans to boost its participation in the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan from 50 troops to 150. 
(HINA, HRT - 20/04/06)
